column69: In my country psychiatrists give too much importance to psychotherapy. We are not enough trained in clinical psychiatry. For this reason our patients go to neurologists to have diagnosis and therapies

column25: Psychoterapy training js essential for a trainee, whatever theory it comes from. I think that a good psychiatrist should be able to use both pharmaceutical and talking care, because every patient need all the good ways to improve his/her mental health. The big problem is that many italian psychiatry recidencies don't have interest and/or money enough to provide this kind or training, and we are supposed to look outside, in private context, for a good training, if we desire for it. This is tough because we need to work a lot and to find out extra work as general doctors to get needed money.
